Step 1. Start by updating the system package index. Launch a terminal window (Ctrl+Alt+T) and 

run the following command:

sudo apt update

Updating the package index ensures you’re working with the latest software versions.

root@DESKTOP-623DOIP:~# sudo apt update

Fetched 15.3 MB in 6s (2540 kB/s)

Reading package lists... Done

Building dependency tree

Reading state information... Done

199 ckages can be upgraded. Run 'apt list --upgradable' to see them.

 Step 2. Install Git from the default Ubuntu repository by running:

 sudo apt install git

root@DESKTOP-623DOIP:~# sudo apt install git

Reading package lists... Done

Building dependency tree

Reading state information... Done

 Step 3. Verify the installation and version by running:

 git –version

root@DESKTOP-623DOIP:~# git --version

git version 2.25.1
